25/05/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- NATO Secretary General Lord George Robertson commended the Romanian Border Police for swift, successful reforms, the Romanian Interior Ministry reported Saturday (24 May). He also recommended that Romania share its experience in border security with other countries in the region. Robertson made the statement on Friday at the last day of the conference for security of borders in Southeast Europe, held in Ohrid, Macedonia. The Romanian delegation included First Deputy Interior Minister Toma Zaharia, Border Police General Inspectorate Chief Aurel Neagu, and foreign ministry officials. (Rompres - 24/05/03)
